    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"the reality is...\"? That sounds pretty one-sided. Don't you think the economic arguments about government inefficiency and the potential for lower quality of care or long wait times are just as valid as the moral ones? Why is the \"moral imperative\" side the only one you're treating as reality?",
